    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PAROLE DELAYS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Laura Mansnerus</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Mansnerus, Laura</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Lawyers say they are prepared to settle suit filed on behalf of New Jersey prison inmates who have become eligible for parole but have not been given mandated hearings (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>While the New Jersey Parole Board struggles with its backlog of cases, lawyers for inmates and the Attorney General's office told a federal judge in Camden Wednesday that they were prepared to settle a lawsuit filed on behalf of prisoners who have become eligible for parole but not given the hearings required by law. Elaine G. Selan, a prison-rights advocate who has been a liaison between the plaintiffs and their lawyers, said the issue remaining was whether and how the state would pay damages.</p>
        <p>Laura Mansnerus</p>
      </block>
